body_md:
Concerns can be raised via the whistleblowing portal or line, Compliance mailbox, or line manager (if appropriate).

{% if whistleChannelsList %}
Available channels:
{{ whistleChannelsList }}
{% endif %}

{% if whistleAnonymous %}
Reports can be anonymous or named. Confidentiality is protected on a need-to-know basis, and data is minimised.
{% endif %}
{% unless whistleAnonymous %}
Reports are expected to be named. Confidentiality is protected on a need-to-know basis, and data is minimised.
{% endunless %}

Where appropriate, concerns may be escalated to regulators.

{% if whistleChampion %}
The Whistleblowing Champion works with Compliance and Legal to manage external notifications.
{% endif %}
{% unless whistleChampion %}
Compliance and Legal manage external notifications and escalation routes.
{% endunless %}

Records must include intake details, investigation steps, outcomes, remediation actions, and timelines.

{% if whistleConcernTypesList %}
Common concern themes tracked include:
{{ whistleConcernTypesList }}
{% endif %}

Management information should track themes, timeliness, and any retaliation concerns for board oversight.
